  "body": "After some discussion with @herumi, he brought a potential optimization when hashing to G2. Currently when hashing a binary string to G2, we multiply it by a large co-factor which is computationally expensive to perform. \r\n\r\nHowever we can utilize a faster co-factor for this based on this paper by [Burdoni and Pintore](https://eprint.iacr.org/2017/419) \r\n\r\n```c\r\n\t\tQ = (z(z-1)-1)P + Frob((z-1)P) + Frob^2(2P)\r\n\t\tfast-cofactor = org-cofactor * X, where X is a fixed constant.\r\n```\r\nAn implementation of the algorithm is over [here](https://github.com/herumi/mcl/blob/master/include/mcl/bn.hpp#L463-L478) .\r\n\r\nHowever the downside that with using the faster co-factor, the value of MapToG2 changes correspondingly. ",
